specs.implementationPlan:
All code goes in src/renderer/js. No new globals beyond WC.Clipboard and WC.Dialogs.clipboardPane.

A) History store + capture (editor-level, in a new IIFE block or appended to commands.js):
- Add WC.Clipboard = { items: [], MAX: 24 } where items[] = { html, text, kind: 'text'|'image', ts }. Newest unshifted to front.
- Capture function: WC.Clipboard.capture(range) reads the current selection's HTML and text BEFORE the browser cut clears it:
    const sel = window.getSelection();
    if (!sel || sel.isCollapsed) return;
    const r = sel.getRangeAt(0);
    const frag = r.cloneContents();
    const div = document.createElement('div'); div.appendChild(frag);
    const html = div.innerHTML.replace(/ŌĆŗ/g,''); // strip zero-width spans used by applyInlineStyle
    const text = sel.toString();
    if (!text.trim() && !div.querySelector('img')) return;
    const kind = (!text.trim() && div.querySelector('img')) ? 'image' : 'text';
    Dedup: if items[0] && items[0].html === html, skip. Else unshift({html,text,kind,ts:Date.now()}); if (items.length > MAX) items.length = MAX.
    Then if pane open, re-render; if 'auto' option on, open pane.
- Wire capture into the existing handlers in commands.js. Change:
    H.cut = () => { WC.Clipboard.capture(); E().exec('cut'); };
    H.copy = () => { WC.Clipboard.capture(); E().exec('copy'); };
  Also intercept native keyboard Ctrl+C / Ctrl+X (since those bypass H.cut/H.copy): in editor.js init(), add
    this.node.addEventListener('copy', () => WC.Clipboard.capture());
    this.node.addEventListener('cut', () => WC.Clipboard.capture());
  (These fire on the editor before the browser mutates the DOM for cut, so cloneContents still has the selection; capture reads the selection synchronously in the event, which is valid.) This single interception covers both ribbon buttons and keyboard, so the ribbon handlers can rely on it OR call capture directly ŌĆö keep capture idempotent via the dedup-on-items[0] guard to avoid double-adds when both the DOM 'copy' event and H.copy fire.
  Cleanest: leave H.cut/H.copy as-is and ONLY capture in the DOM 'copy'/'cut' listeners ŌĆö that covers ribbon-triggered execCommand('copy') too, because execCommand('copy') dispatches a real 'copy' event. Dedup guard then prevents duplicates. Prefer this approach (one capture site).

B) Paste an item: WC.Clipboard.paste(item):
    E().focus(); E().restoreRange();
    if (item.kind === 'image' || /</.test(item.html)) E().insertHTML(item.html);
    else E().insertHTML(WC.escapeHtml(item.text).replace(/\n/g,'<br>'));
  (insertHTML routes through E().exec('insertHTML', ...) which keeps caret/repaginate/emit.)
  WC.Clipboard.pasteAll(): iterate items from OLDEST to newest (items.slice().reverse()), calling paste() for each so document order matches collection order.

C) Task pane: add D.clipboardPane to dialogs.js, mirroring D.navPane/D.stylesPane exactly:
    D.clipboardPane = function () {
      let pane = document.getElementById('clipboard-pane'); if (pane) { pane.remove(); return; } // toggle
      pane = el('div', { class: 'taskpane', id: 'clipboard-pane' });
      head = .tp-head with title 'Clipboard' + close X (onclick remove).
      actions row: two el('button',{class:'btn'...}) Paste All -> WC.Clipboard.pasteAll(); Clear All -> WC.Clipboard.clear().
      count line .cb-count.
      body .tp-body > list .cb-list.
      render() builds rows from WC.Clipboard.items; each .cb-item: icon span, preview span (text: item.text.slice(0,50) + (len>50?'ŌĆ”':'') OR an <img src> thumbnail at max-height 40px for image kind), chevron .cb-item-menu opening WC.flyout with Paste / Delete.
      item body click -> WC.Clipboard.paste(item).
      Disable Paste All/Clear All buttons + show placeholder when items empty.
      Append pane to document.getElementById('workarea') (same host the other panes use).
      Register WC.Clipboard.onChange = render so capture()/clear()/delete re-render live (guard for pane removed: re-query getElementById and bail if gone).
    }
  WC.Clipboard methods clear() (items.length=0; onChange()), remove(idx) (items.splice(idx,1); onChange()).

D) Dispatch wiring: add handler in commands.js so the existing launcher (ribbon-data home.clipboard.clipboard, cmd 'clipboard') opens the pane instead of falling through to notImplemented:
    H.clipboard = () => WC.Dialogs.clipboardPane();
  No ribbon-data change needed ŌĆö the launcher already exists with cmd:'clipboard' and Commands.run dispatches H[cmd].

E) CSS: append to src/renderer/styles/dialogs.css (reuse .taskpane shell):
    .cb-actions { display:flex; gap:6px; padding:8px 0; }
    .cb-actions .btn { flex:1; }
    .cb-count { font-size:12px; color:#666; padding:0 0 6px; }
    .cb-item { display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:8px; padding:8px; border:1px solid #edebe9; border-radius:2px; margin-bottom:6px; cursor:pointer; position:relative; }
    .cb-item:hover { background:var(--word-blue-tint); border-color:var(--word-blue); }
    .cb-item .cb-ic { flex:0 0 18px; color:#666; }
    .cb-item .cb-prev { font-size:12px; line-height:1.35; color:#222; overflow:hidden; }
    .cb-item img.cb-thumb { max-height:40px; max-width:100%; }
    .cb-item-menu { position:absolute; top:4px; right:4px; opacity:0; cursor:pointer; }
    .cb-item:hover .cb-item-menu { opacity:1; }
    .cb-empty { color:#888; text-align:center; padding:24px 8px; font-size:13px; }
  Optionally add a 'clipboard' icon to icons.js (a simple clipboard path) and use WC.icon('clipboard',16) for .cb-ic; otherwise reuse WC.icon('_generic',14).

Load order: util.js/editor.js/dialogs.js/commands.js are all already loaded; WC.Clipboard can live at the top of commands.js (or its own small file added to index.html script list) since it is referenced lazily inside handlers/the pane.

All changes live in commands.js (the painter state already exists there) plus one ribbon wiring hook and a small CSS rule. Concrete steps:

1) commands.js ŌĆö STATE. Keep the existing module var `let painter = null`. Extend its shape to `{ inline, block, sticky }`. Add `let fpArmed = false` only if needed; simpler is to treat `painter !== null` as "armed".

2) commands.js ŌĆö CAPTURE. Replace currentInlineStyle() with a richer copier `captureFormat()` returning `{ inline:{...}, block:{...} }`:
   - inline (from getComputedStyle of the run at sel.anchorNodeŌåÆ nearest element): fontFamily, fontSize, fontWeight, fontStyle, textDecorationLine, textDecorationStyle, textDecorationColor, color, backgroundColor, verticalAlign (for sub/superscript), fontVariantCaps, letterSpacing.
   - block (from the nearest block via E().selectedBlocks()[0]): only captured when the selection spans/touches a whole block (sel.isCollapsed OR selection covers block startŌåÆend). Capture textAlign, lineHeight, marginTop, marginBottom, textIndent, paddingLeft (indent). Store the block tagName/className too so a paragraph "style" can be re-applied.

3) commands.js ŌĆö H.formatPainter (single click). Keep current behavior but route through a new `armPainter(node, sticky)`:
   H.formatPainter = (c, node) => armPainterFromSelection(node, false);
   where armPainterFromSelection(node,sticky){ painter = { ...captureFormat(), sticky }; setPainterUI(node, true, sticky); WC.toast(sticky ? 'Format Painter locked ŌĆö select text to apply repeatedly; Esc or click to stop.' : 'Format Painter ŌĆö select text to apply the copied formatting once.'); }

4) commands.js ŌĆö DOUBLE-CLICK detection. ribbon.js renders plain buttons with a single 'click' listener (ribbon.js:211). Add a hook so cmd==='formatPainter' also binds 'dblclick'. Minimal, localized change in ribbon.js renderControl else-branch:
   if (c.cmd === 'formatPainter') node.addEventListener('dblclick', () => { WC.closeFlyouts(); WC.Commands.run({ cmd: 'formatPainterLock' }, node); });
   Then add H.formatPainterLock = (c, node2) => { const node = node2 || WC.Ribbon.controlIndex['formatPainter'].node; armPainterFromSelection(node, true); }.
   Note: the single 'click' fires before 'dblclick'; that is fine because both just (re)capture and re-arm ŌĆö the second event upgrades sticky=falseŌåÆtrue. To avoid the click also consuming a one-shot apply, capture happens on the button, not the editor, so the leading click does not apply anything.

5) commands.js ŌĆö APPLY (the editor mouseup handler). Bind ONE persistent handler on E().node when arming, removed on disarm. On editor mouseup:
   - if !painter return; if selection collapsed return;
   - build a span, Object.assign painter.inline onto span.style (skip backgroundColor when 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)'/'transparent'); surroundContents with extractContents fallback (same pattern as existing armPainter, commands.js:189-190);
   - if painter.block was captured AND the selection covers whole blocks: E().selectedBlocks().forEach(b => Object.assign(b.style, painter.block)) and, if a style/tag was stored, optionally WC.applyNamedStyle / formatBlock.
   - E().dirty=true; E().repaginate(); E().updateStatus(); E().emit();
   - if (!painter.sticky) disarmPainter(node);  // one-shot: revert after first apply.

6) commands.js ŌĆö DISARM + UI. 
   function disarmPainter(node){ painter=null; E().node.classList.remove('fp-active'); E().node.removeEventListener('mouseup', applyHandler); if(node) node.classList.remove('toggled'); }
   function setPainterUI(node, on, sticky){ E().node.classList.toggle('fp-active', on); if(node) node.classList.toggle('toggled', on); }
   Use a single named module-level applyHandler so add/removeEventListener pair correctly (the current code creates a fresh closure each time, which leaks listeners across re-arms ŌĆö fix by hoisting one handler).

7) commands.js ŌĆö Esc + re-click cancel. 
   - Re-click: in armPainterFromSelection, if painter already armed and same node clicked while sticky ŌåÆ toggle off (disarm). Practically: if (painter) { disarmPainter(node); return; } at the top of the single/lock arm path so a click on an armed button cancels it (Word toggles off on re-click).
   - Esc: extend the existing global keydown in app.js:52. Add WC.Commands.cancelFormatPainter && WC.Commands.cancelFormatPainter(); inside the Escape branch (before/after closeFlyouts). Expose Commands.cancelFormatPainter = () => { if (painter) disarmPainter(WC.Ribbon.controlIndex['formatPainter'].node); };

8) commands.js ŌĆö Keyboard Ctrl+Shift+C / Ctrl+Shift+V. Add to app.js keymap: (k==='c' && shift) => arm one-shot capture (painter set, sticky=false, no UI lock needed but set fp-active); (k==='v' && shift) => apply captured format to current selection immediately (reuse the apply body, then if !sticky disarm). These are optional polish but advertised in the tooltip, so wire them for fidelity.

9) CSS ŌĆö editor.css. Add:
   #editor.fp-active, #editor.fp-active * { cursor: url("data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='20' height='20' viewBox='0 0 20 20'><path d='M3 17l2-5 6-6 3 3-6 6-5 2z' fill='%232B579A'/><path d='M11 6l3-3 3 3-3 3z' fill='%23C0C0C0'/></svg>") 3 17, text; }
   (paintbrush hotspot near the tip; falls back to text I-beam.)

Files touched: src/renderer/js/commands.js (main logic), src/renderer/js/ribbon.js (one dblclick hook for cmd formatPainter), src/renderer/js/app.js (Esc cancel + optional Ctrl+Shift+C/V), src/renderer/styles/editor.css (fp-active cursor). No new globals beyond Commands.cancelFormatPainter; reuses WC.Editor, WC.toast, WC.Ribbon.controlIndex, .toggled class.
